        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2019-07-31 20:07:15.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nBobi,\n\nI'd like to review this one, so my question stands - What exactly is accessing aa_oa after it's been freed?  I poked around and didn't see anything.\n\nIt's obviously fine to clear it, I'd just like to understand the problem better.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "288746bad8eac1786853b4fa2bbca1b6e2705c35",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2019-07-31 20:37:27.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n> I'd like to review this one, so my question stands - What exactly\n > is accessing aa_oa after it's been freed?  I poked around and\n > didn't see anything.\n > \n > It's obviously fine to clear it, I'd just like to understand the\n > problem better.\n\nPatrick, my understanding is that the \"aa_oa\" part is from the local prlrpc_req struct and that may be accessed again directly from the req.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "e354529686b73b5302aa7de3e098a6cf31a1fd22",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 797,
        "name": "Patrick Farrell",
        "email": "pfarrell@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "pfarrell",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2019-07-31 20:54:24.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nHm, OK - but perhaps another way to look at it:\nWhere is the aa_oa field accessed that checks if it's NULL first?  I'm not finding anywhere, as far as I can see it's just accessed unconditionally.\n\nWe're just clearing the pointer, so unless someone's checking if it's NULL, then instead of user after free we'll just get a null pointer.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "27b111e420be13f19fec4fba0b218a6295bc5762",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 103,
        "name": "Zhenyu Xu",
        "email": "bobijam@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "bobijam"
      },
      "date": "2019-08-29 02:30:26.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n> Hm, OK - but perhaps another way to look at it:\n > Where is the aa_oa field accessed that checks if it's NULL first? \n > I'm not finding anywhere, as far as I can see it's just accessed\n > unconditionally.\n > \n > We're just clearing the pointer, so unless someone's checking if\n > it's NULL, then instead of user after free we'll just get a null\n > pointer.\n\nThere is a freechain corruption \n\n > Hm, OK - but perhaps another way to look at it:\n > Where is the aa_oa field accessed that checks if it's NULL first? \n > I'm not finding anywhere, as far as I can see it's just accessed\n > unconditionally.\n > \n > We're just clearing the pointer, so unless someone's checking if\n > it's NULL, then instead of user after free we'll just get a null\n > pointer.\n\nThere is a freechain corruption in HP-246, and I suspect aa_oa could be the victim, so I add this hoping to reveal where possible access after free happens.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
